 4881:   422: <file path=".github/skills/human-in-the-loop/SKILL.md">
 4882:   423:  1: # Human In The Loop (HITL)
 4883:   424:  2: 
 4884:   425:  3: ## Purpose
 4885:   426:  4: 
 4886:   427:  5: Asegurar confirmacion humana solo cuando una decision o accion tiene riesgo alto, impacto externo o potencial destructivo.
 4887:   428:  6: 
 4888:   429:  7: ## Scope
 4889:   430:  8: 
 4890:   431:  9: Aplicar en todas las rutas del sistema como capa transversal.
 4891:   432: 10: 
 4892:   433: 11: ## Always-On Behavior
 4893:   434: 12: 
 4894:   435: 13: - Deteccion automatica de riesgo desde intent/domain/source/notes de routing.
 4895:   436: 14: - No pedir confirmacion para rutas de bajo riesgo.
 4896:   437: 15: - Pedir confirmacion cuando exista riesgo alto o fallback de routing.
 4897:   438: 16: - Bloquear ejecucion para acciones destructivas hasta aprobacion explicita.
 4898:   439: 17: 
 4899:   440: 18: ## Risk Triggers
 4900:   441: 19: 
 4901:   442: 20: - deploy, production
 4902:   443: 21: - migrate, migration
 4903:   444: 22: - delete, drop, destroy, remove
 4904:   445: 23: - governance, policy
 4905:   446: 24: - security, rbac, role
 4906:   447: 25: - unresolved_dependencies
 4907:   448: 26: - routing_fallback
 4908:   449: 27: 
 4909:   450: 28: ## Actions
 4910:   451: 29: 
 4911:   452: 30: - `none`: continuar sin aprobacion.
 4912:   453: 31: - `request_human_confirmation`: solicitar confirmacion antes de ejecutar.
 4913:   454: 32: - `block_until_human_approval`: bloquear hasta aprobacion humana.
 4914:   455: 33: 
 4915:   456: 34: ## Observability Contract
 4916:   457: 35: 
 4917:   458: 36: Cada evento de routing debe incluir `hitl`:
 4918:   459: 37: 
 4919:   460: 38: - `mode`: `always_on_auto`
 4920:   461: 39: - `required`: `true|false`
 4921:   462: 40: - `action`: `none|request_human_confirmation|block_until_human_approval`
 4922:   463: 41: - `reason`: motivo legible y trazable
 4923:   464: 42: 
 4924:   465: 43: ## Guardrails
 4925:   466: 44: 
 4926:   467: 45: - Nunca cachear secretos, credenciales, tokens o PII.
 4927:   468: 46: - Si hay duda de sensibilidad, declarar gap y no cachear.
 4928:   469: 47: - Confirmaciones humanas solo para impacto real; evitar friccion en bajo riesgo.
 4929:   470: </file>
 4930:   471: <file path=".github/workflows/routing-evals.yml">
 4931:   472:   1: name: Routing Evals Gate
 4932:   473:   2: on:
 4933:   474:   3:   pull_request:
 4934:   475:   4:   push:
 4935:   476:   5:     branches:
 4936:   477:   6:       - main
 4937:   478:   7:   workflow_dispatch:
 4938:   479:   8: permissions:
 4939:   480:   9:   contents: read
 4940:   481:  10: concurrency:
 4941:   482:  11:   group: routing-evals-${{ github.ref }}
 4942:   483:  12:   cancel-in-progress: true
 4943:   484:  13: jobs:
 4944:   485:  14:   routing-evals:
 4945:   486:  15:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 4946:   487:  16:     timeout-minutes: 15
 4947:   488:  17:     env:
 4948:   489:  18:       PYTHONUNBUFFERED: '1'
 4949:   490:  19:     steps:
 4950:   491:  20:       - name: Checkout
 4951:   492:  21:         uses: actions/checkout@v4
 4952:   493:  22:         with:
 4953:   494:  23:           fetch-depth: 1
 4954:   495:  24:       - name: Set up Python
 4955:   496:  25:         uses: actions/setup-python@v5
 4956:   497:  26:         with:
 4957:   498:  27:           python-version: '3.12'
 4958:   499:  28:           cache: 'pip'
 4959:   500:  29:           cache-dependency-path: requirements.txt
 4960:   501:  30:       - name: Upgrade pip
 4961:   502:  31:         run: python -m pip install --upgrade pip
 4962:   503:  32:       - name: Install dependencies (if requirements.txt exists)
 4963:   504:  33:         run: |
 4964:   505:  34:           if [ -f requirements.txt ]; then
 4965:   506:  35:             python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
 4966:   507:  36:           fi
 4967:   508:  37:       - name: Run routing evals
 4968:   509:  38:         run: python ./scripts/intake/run-routing-evals.py
 4969:   510:  39:       - name: Build learning loop report
 4970:   511:  40:         run: python ./scripts/learning/learning-loop-report.py
 4971:   512:  41:       - name: Build iteration value report
 4972:   513:  42:         run: python ./scripts/learning/iteration-value-report.py
 4973:   514:  43:       - name: Enforce AutoLearning gate
 4974:   515:  44:         run: python ./scripts/learning/autolearning-gate.py
 4975:   516:  45:       - name: Enforce zero failed cases
 4976:   517:  46:         run: |
 4977:   518:  47:           python - <<'PY'
 4978:   519:  48:           import json
 4979:   520:  49:           from pathlib import Path
 4980:   521:  50:           report = Path('observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json')
 4981:   522:  51:           if not report.exists():
 4982:   523:  52:               raise SystemExit('routing-eval-report.json not found')
 4983:   524:  53:           data = json.loads(report.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
 4984:   525:  54:           failed = int(data.get('cases_failed', 0))
 4985:   526:  55:           total = int(data.get('cases_total', 0))
 4986:   527:  56:           passed = int(data.get('cases_passed', 0))
 4987:   528:  57:           print(f'Routing evals: {passed}/{total} passed, failed={failed}')
 4988:   529:  58:           if failed > 0:
 4989:   530:  59:               raise SystemExit(1)
 4990:   531:  60:           PY
 4991:   532:  61:       - name: Upload eval artifacts
 4992:   533:  62:         if: always()
 4993:   534:  63:         uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
 4994:   535:  64:         with:
 4995:   536:  65:           name: routing-evals-${{ github.run_number }}
 4996:   537:  66:           if-no-files-found: warn
 4997:   538:  67:           path: |
 4998:   539:  68:             observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json
 4999:   540:  69:             observability/evals/learning-loop-report.json
 5000:   541:  70:             observability/evals/learning-loop-report.md
 5001:   542:  71:             observability/evals/iteration-value-report.json
 5002:   543:  72:             observability/evals/iteration-value-report.md
 5003:   544:  73:   publish-summary:
 5004:   545:  74:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 5005:   546:  75:     timeout-minutes: 5
 5006:   547:  76:     needs:
 5007:   548:  77:       - routing-evals
 5008:   549:  78:     if: always()
 5009:   550:  79:     steps:
 5010:   551:  80:       - name: Download eval artifacts
 5011:   552:  81:         id: download_artifacts
 5012:   553:  82:         continue-on-error: true
 5013:   554:  83:         uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
 5014:   555:  84:         with:
 5015:   556:  85:           name: routing-evals-${{ github.run_number }}
 5016:   557:  86:           path: artifacts
 5017:   558:  87:       - name: Publish workflow summary
 5018:   559:  88:         if: always()
 5019:   560:  89:         run: |
 5020:   561:  90:           python - <<'PY'
 5021:   562:  91:           import json
 5022:   563:  92:           import os
 5023:   564:  93:           from pathlib import Path
 5024:   565:  94:           summary_path = Path(os.environ['GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY'])
 5025:   566:  95:           routing = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/routing-eval-report.json')
 5026:   567:  96:           learning = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/learning-loop-report.json')
 5027:   568:  97:           iteration = Path('artifacts/observability/evals/iteration-value-report.json')
 5028:   569:  98:           lines = ['# Routing Evals Summary', '']
 5029:   570:  99:           lines.append(f"- routing-evals result: {os.environ.get('NEEDS_ROUTING_EVALS_RESULT', 'unknown')}")
 5030:   571: 100:           lines.append('')
 5031:   572: 101:           if routing.exists():
 5032:   573: 102:               data = json.loads(routing.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
 5033:   574: 103:               total = int(data.get('cases_total', 0))
 5034:   575: 104:               passed = int(data.get('cases_passed', 0))
 5035:   576: 105:               failed = int(data.get('cases_failed', 0))
 5036:   577: 106:               lines.extend([
 5037:   578: 107:                   '## Routing Gate',
 5038:   579: 108:                   f'- total: {total}',
 5039:   580: 109:                   f'- passed: {passed}',
 5040:   581: 110:                   f'- failed: {failed}',
 5041:   582: 111:                   ''
 5042:   583: 112:               ])
 5043:   584: 113:           else:
 5044:   585: 114:               lines.extend(['## Routing Gate', '- report missing', ''])
 5045:   586: 115:           if learning.exists():
 5046:   587: 116:               data = json.loads(learning.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
 5047:   588: 117:               kpis = data.get('kpis', {}) if isinstance(data.get('kpis', {}), dict) else {}
 5048:   589: 118:               lines.extend([
 5049:   590: 119:                   '## Learning Loop',
 5050:   591: 120:                   f"- fallback_rate: {kpis.get('fallback_rate', 0.0)}",
 5051:   592: 121:                   f"- grounded_rate: {kpis.get('grounded_rate', 0.0)}",
 5052:   593: 122:                   f"- success_rate: {kpis.get('success_rate', 0.0)}",
 5053:   594: 123:                   f"- confidence_avg: {kpis.get('confidence_avg', 0.0)}",
 5054:   595: 124:                   ''
 5055:   596: 125:               ])
 5056:   597: 126:           else:
 5057:   598: 127:               lines.extend(['## Learning Loop', '- report missing', ''])
 5058:   599: 128:           if iteration.exists():
 5059:   600: 129:               data = json.loads(iteration.read_text(encoding='utf-8'))
 5060:   601: 130:               kpis = data.get('kpis', {}) if isinstance(data.get('kpis', {}), dict) else {}
 5061:   602: 131:               lines.extend([
 5062:   603: 132:                   '## Iteration Value',
 5063:   604: 133:                   f"- metrics_coverage_rate: {kpis.get('metrics_coverage_rate', 0.0)}",
 5064:   605: 134:                   f"- confirmed_feedback_rate: {kpis.get('confirmed_feedback_rate', 0.0)}",
 5065:   606: 135:                   f"- confirmed_success_rate: {kpis.get('confirmed_success_rate', 0.0)}",
 5066:   607: 136:                   f"- total_tokens: {kpis.get('total_tokens', 0)}",
 5067:   608: 137:                   f"- total_cost_usd: {kpis.get('total_cost_usd', 0.0)}",
 5068:   609: 138:                   ''
 5069:   610: 139:               ])
 5070:   611: 140:           else:
 5071:   612: 141:               lines.extend(['## Iteration Value', '- report missing', ''])
 5072:   613: 142:           summary_path.write_text('\n'.join(lines) + '\n', encoding='utf-8')
 5073:   614: 143:           PY
 5074:   615: 144:         env:
 5075:   616: 145:           NEEDS_ROUTING_EVALS_RESULT: ${{ needs.routing-evals.result }}
