14600: 10141:  1: # Cross Memory Reasoning
14601: 10142:  2: 
14602: 10143:  3: Used when a query touches multiple domains.
14603: 10144:  4: 
14604: 10145:  5: Example:
14605: 10146:  6: 
14606: 10147:  7: - code + SLA
14607: 10148:  8: - DBA + architecture
14608: 10149:  9: - docs + business
14609: 10150: 10: 
14610: 10151: 11: Process:
14611: 10152: 12: 
14612: 10153: 13: 1. Query each memory
14613: 10154: 14: 2. Extract relevant signals
14614: 10155: 15: 3. Merge into unified response
14615: 10156: 16: 4. If source is code, resolve symbols via CodeGraph before broad file reads
14616: 10157: 17: 5. Register reusable pattern in code-memory feedback loop
14617: 10158: </file>
